Notes:

Date:  4/6/1910
Source:  Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  10
Edition:
Quote:  The ferns, which attain the size of trees, are the splendid long-fronded mamaku with its black trunk, the mauku and tuakura, and the smaller ones are the wheki, the maru, and the taiwhaniwha [sic], the heruheru [todeamedia), and that queen of the New Zealand fern tribe, the tete or todea superba, commonly known as the "Prince of Wales' Feather."
